  <h1>STORY OF MY FAVOURITE COLOR</h1>
  
  <h3>When I was younger I loved pink a lot, but growing up I suddenly disliked it. I don't really know the reason behind disliking what I first liked (PINK). I think it's because I see it as a childish color, or I don't really know. Funny enough, I see adults who tag pink as a favorite color and it makes me wonder. Everybody is different. Even girls who like pink as a favorite color seem dull (BARBIE) to me.</h3>
  
  <h3>Now that I'm grown up, I just seem to like red and black, especially black. But then in the geography that I am in, black is used to mourn the dead or for acting the devil in a drama scene. Nevertheless, I still love black, to the point that my earrings are all black, my school course in LAW has a black-and-white uniform, and my department in church is MEDIA. My love for black is second to none.</h3>
  
  <h3>Now let's talk about my love for red. I love pepper red, not just any type of red. Red is also used to scare people away from stealing in my location and for acting the devil's part in a drama scene. But I still love red. I don’t know if people can have two favorite colors, but mine are <em>RED AND BLACK</em>.</h3>
  
